# React + shadcn/ui + TypeScript Best Practices

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/                  # Pages / route segments (Next.js) or route files
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # shadcn/ui primitives (auto-generated — do not edit manually)
│   └── <feature>/        # Composed, feature-specific components
├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
├── lib/                  # Utilities, helpers, shadcn's `cn()` util
├── types/                # Shared TypeScript types and interfaces
└── services/             # API calls, data-fetching logic
```

- Keep `components/ui/` **untouched** — treat shadcn files as third-party primitives
- Build feature components by **composing** shadcn primitives, never duplicating their logic
- Co-locate component-specific styles, hooks, and tests with the component file

---

## TypeScript

- Enable **strict mode** in `tsconfig.json` (`"strict": true`) — never disable it to silence errors
- Prefer **`interface`** for object shapes that may be extended; use **`type`** for unions, intersections, and mapped types
- Avoid `any` — use `unknown` and narrow it properly; prefer explicit generic constraints
- Use **discriminated unions** for state machines and variant props:
  ```ts
  type ButtonState =
    | { status: 'idle' }
    | { status: 'loading' }
    | { status: 'error'; message: string };
  ```
- Export component prop types so consumers can reference them:
  ```ts
  export interface CardHeaderProps { title: string; subtitle?: string; }
  ```
- Use **`satisfies`** operator to validate objects without widening their type
- Prefer `const` assertions for literal objects used as lookup tables

---

## Component Design

### General Rules
- Prefer **functional components** with hooks — never class components in new code
- One component per file; file name matches the exported component name
- Keep components **small and focused** — extract sub-components when JSX exceeds ~100 lines
- Separate **container logic** (data fetching, state) from **presentational rendering**

### Props
- Destructure props directly in the function signature for clarity
- Use **optional chaining and default values** in destructuring instead of `||` guards:
  ```tsx
  function Badge({ label, variant = 'default' }: BadgeProps) { ... }
  ```
- Extend HTML element props with `React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<'div'>` when wrapping native elements — forward all standard attributes and the `ref`

### Using shadcn/ui
- Import shadcn primitives from `@/components/ui/*` — never import from `radix-ui` directly in feature code
- Use the `cn()` utility (from `lib/utils`) to merge Tailwind classes conditionally:
  ```tsx
  import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
  <div className={cn('rounded-md p-4', isActive && 'bg-primary text-white', className)} />
  ```
- Extend shadcn components through **className props and CVA variants** rather than wrapping them in extra DOM nodes
- Use `asChild` for composition without extra DOM elements:
  ```tsx
  <Button asChild><Link href="/about">About</Link></Button>
  ```
- Add **custom variants** via `class-variance-authority` (CVA) — never hard-code one-off variant logic inline

---

## Hooks

- Prefix custom hooks with `use`; keep them in `src/hooks/`
- Custom hooks should have a **single, clear responsibility**
- Keep `useEffect` dependencies **complete and minimal** — address every ESLint exhaustive-deps warning
- Use `useCallback` and `useMemo` **only when profiling shows a real performance problem**; premature memoisation hurts readability
- Fetch data with **TanStack Query** (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) or SWR instead of raw `useEffect` + `useState` pairs

---

## State Management

- **Local state first** (`useState`, `useReducer`) — reach for global state only when truly needed
- Use `useReducer` when state transitions are complex or interdependent
- For global state, prefer **Zustand** or **Jotai** over heavy solutions like Redux unless the project already uses them
- Derive computed values rather than storing redundant state

---

## Forms

- Use **React Hook Form** for all non-trivial forms; integrate with `zod` for schema validation
- Use shadcn's `<Form>` components (built on React Hook Form) for consistent styling
- Validate on both client and server — never trust only client-side validation

---

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS utility classes** exclusively; avoid writing custom CSS unless unavoidable
- Extract repeated class combinations into **CVA variants** or shared component wrappers — not into separate CSS files
- Use the design tokens from `tailwind.config` (colours, spacing, typography) — never hard-code hex values
- Dark mode: use Tailwind's `dark:` variant with shadcn's `ThemeProvider`

---

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML first; reach for `<div>` or `<span>` only when no semantic element fits
- shadcn components handle ARIA for you — do not override `role`, `aria-*`, or keyboard behaviour unless you know exactly what you are doing
- Every `<img>` must have meaningful `alt` text (or `alt=""` for decorative images)
- All interactive elements must be reachable and operable via keyboard alone

---

## File & Naming Conventions

| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Components | `PascalCase.tsx` | `UserAvatar.tsx` |
| Hooks | `camelCase.ts` prefixed `use` | `useCurrentUser.ts` |
| Utilities | `camelCase.ts` | `formatDate.ts` |
| Types | `PascalCase` | `interface UserProfile {}` |
| Constants | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `MAX_RETRIES` |

---

## Performance

- Use **`React.lazy` + `Suspense`** for route-level and heavy component code splitting
- Avoid passing new object/array literals or inline arrow functions as props to memoised components — they break memoisation on every render
- Profile with React DevTools Profiler before optimising — measure, don't guess

## Testing

- Use **Vitest** + **React Testing Library** (or Jest if the project already uses it)
- Test **user-visible behaviour**, not implementation details (no snapshot tests of raw HTML)
- Mock only at network/service boundaries (MSW for API mocks)

---

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

- ❌ Direct DOM manipulation (`document.querySelector`) — use refs instead
- ❌ `useEffect` for derived state — compute it during render
- ❌ Prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use context or a state manager
- ❌ Storing server state in `useState` — use a data-fetching library
- ❌ Modifying shadcn component source files — override via className and variants
